<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1256" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1256">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/178a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Bevan</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>If an engagement is threatened near Tampico, you will please confer
                            immediately with the respective leaders and caution them against the
                            destruction of the oil properties, pointing out the danger of
                            conflagration and the possibility of great damage being done to both
                            life and property.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>